  "narrative": {
    "intro": "This ranking lists the largest federal contracts by total value for FY2026 to date and highlights the top awardees by full contract value. Total obligations for the period are $51.3B. The largest single contract holder on the list is HUMANA GOVERNMENT BUSINESS INC with $51.3B in total award value, followed by major defense and national-laboratory contractors including LOCKHEED MARTIN CORP ($48.1B), NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC ($42.6B), and UT-BATTELLE LLC ($42.1B). Several national-security and research institutions also appear among the top ten: LAWRENCE LIVERMORE NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC ($41.2B), REGENTS OF THE UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA, THE ($35.3B), and TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC ($35B). Shipbuilding and aerospace firms show up as well, with ELECTRIC BOAT CORPORATION ($34.9B), CONSOLIDATED NUCLEAR SECURITY, LLC ($34.3B), and THE BOEING COMPANY ($32B). Note that total award value figures are full contract values, not single-year obligations, so the ranking reflects cumulative contract value rather than FY2026 cash flow alone.",
